---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = "Privacy Policy | Wright Construction Management";
const description = "Privacy Policy for Wright Construction Management LLC — how we collect, use, disclose, and protect information when you interact with WrightCM.co.";
---
<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="page-banner"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> / Privacy Policy</div>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Effective Date: 6/17/26 &middot; Website: WrightCM.co &middot; Company: Wright Construction Management LLC</p>
  </div></section>

  <section><div class="wrap"><div class="legal">
    <p>Wright Construction Management LLC (&ldquo;Wright Construction Management,&rdquo; &ldquo;WCM,&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;our,&rdquo; or &ldquo;us&rdquo;) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect information when you visit our website, WrightCM.co, contact us, submit information through our website, or otherwise interact with us online.</p>
    <p>By using our website, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
    <h3>Information You Provide Directly</h3>
    <p>When you contact us through our website, request information, schedule a call, download a resource, or otherwise communicate with us, we may collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Name</li>
      <li>Company name</li>
      <li>Job title</li>
      <li>Email address</li>
      <li>Phone number</li>
      <li>Project location</li>
      <li>Project details or construction-related information you choose to provide</li>
      <li>Any other information you voluntarily submit through forms, email, phone, or other communications</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Information Collected Automatically</h3>
    <p>When you visit WrightCM.co, we may automatically collect certain information through cookies, analytics tools, server logs, or similar technologies, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>IP address</li>
      <li>Browser type</li>
      <li>Device type</li>
      <li>Operating system</li>
      <li>Pages visited</li>
      <li>Time spent on the website</li>
      <li>Referring website or source</li>
      <li>General location information</li>
      <li>Website usage and interaction data</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Information from Third-Party Tools</h3>
    <p>We may use third-party tools or service providers to help operate our website and business, such as:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Website hosting providers</li>
      <li>Analytics tools, such as Google Analytics or similar tools</li>
      <li>Contact form providers</li>
      <li>CRM or email marketing platforms</li>
      <li>Scheduling tools</li>
      <li>Advertising or remarketing platforms, if used</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These third parties may collect information in accordance with their own privacy policies.</p>

    <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>We may use the information we collect to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Respond to inquiries</li>
      <li>Evaluate potential projects</li>
      <li>Schedule calls or consultations</li>
      <li>Provide information about our services</li>
      <li>Send business communications</li>
      <li>Improve our website and user experience</li>
      <li>Analyze website traffic and marketing performance</li>
      <li>Maintain website security</li>
      <li>Prevent fraud, misuse, or unauthorized access</li>
      <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
      <li>Enforce our rights, agreements, and policies</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information in the ordinary sense of the word.</p>

    <h2>3. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <p>This website uses cookies and similar technologies to improve functionality, analyze website traffic, and support marketing efforts. Cookies are small files stored on your device that help websites recognize your browser and remember certain information. By continuing to use this website, you agree to our use of cookies as described in our Privacy Policy.</p>
    <p>You may be able to disable cookies through your browser settings. However, disabling cookies may affect how certain parts of the website function.</p>
    <p>If we use third-party analytics or advertising tools, those providers may collect information about your activity on our website and other websites over time.</p>

    <h2>4. How We Share Information</h2>
    <p>We may share information with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Service providers who help us operate our website, communications, CRM, marketing, scheduling, analytics, or business systems</li>
      <li>Professional advisors, such as attorneys, accountants, consultants, or insurers</li>
      <li>Business partners or subcontractors, when necessary to evaluate or respond to a project inquiry</li>
      <li>Government authorities, courts, regulators, or law enforcement when required by law</li>
      <li>Successors in interest in connection with a merger, acquisition, restructuring, sale of assets, or similar transaction</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not knowingly share personal information with third parties for their independent marketing purposes unless you have consented or unless otherwise disclosed.</p>

    <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We use reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards designed to protect the information we collect. However, no website, email system, or internet transmission is completely secure. You should avoid submitting highly sensitive information through our website forms unless specifically requested through a secure channel.</p>
    <p>The FTC recommends that businesses collect only what they need, keep it secure, and dispose of it properly. (<a href="https://www.ftc.gov/business-guidance/privacy-security" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Federal Trade Commission</a>)</p>

    <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain information for as long as reasonably necessary to fulfill the purposes described in this Privacy Policy, including to respond to inquiries, maintain business records, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce agreements.</p>
    <p>Retention periods may vary depending on the type of information and the purpose for which it was collected.</p>

    <h2>7. Your Choices</h2>
    <p>You may contact us to request that we:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Update your contact information</li>
      <li>Remove you from marketing communications</li>
      <li>Delete certain personal information, where legally required or reasonably possible</li>
      <li>Provide information about the personal information we maintain about you, where required by applicable law</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You may opt out of marketing emails by following the unsubscribe instructions included in those emails or by contacting us directly.</p>
    <p>Please note that we may retain certain information as necessary for legitimate business purposes, legal compliance, recordkeeping, dispute resolution, or enforcement of agreements.</p>

    <h2>8. Do Not Track Signals</h2>
    <p>Some browsers may transmit &ldquo;Do Not Track&rdquo; signals. Because there is no uniform industry standard for responding to these signals, our website may not respond to them.</p>

    <h2>9. Third-Party Links</h2>
    <p>Our website may contain links to third-party websites, platforms, or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices, content, or security of those third-party websites. You should review the privacy policies of any third-party websites you visit.</p>

    <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>Our website is intended for business and professional audiences. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take reasonable steps to delete it.</p>

    <h2>11. State Privacy Rights</h2>
    <p>Depending on where you live, you may have certain privacy rights under applicable state privacy laws. These rights may include the right to access, correct, delete, or obtain a copy of certain personal information, and the right to opt out of certain types of data sharing or targeted advertising.</p>
    <p>For example, the California Consumer Privacy Act gives certain California residents rights regarding personal information collected by covered businesses. (<a href="https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa" target="_blank" rel="noopener">California DOJ Attorney General</a>)</p>
    <p>Wright Construction Management LLC is based in Illinois and primarily provides construction management and related services. Some state privacy laws only apply to businesses that meet specific thresholds related to revenue, number of consumers, or data-sharing activities. If we are legally required to honor a state-specific privacy request, we will do so.</p>
    <p>To submit a privacy request, please contact us using the information below.</p>

    <h2>12. International Visitors</h2>
    <p>Our website is intended primarily for users located in the United States. If you access our website from outside the United States, you understand that your information may be transferred to, stored, and processed in the United States, where privacy laws may differ from those in your jurisdiction.</p>

    <h2>13. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we update the policy, we will revise the &ldquo;Effective Date&rdquo; above. Your continued use of the website after any changes means you accept the updated Privacy Policy.</p>

    <h2>14. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>For questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at:</p>
    <p>Wright Construction Management LLC<br />
    Website: www.WrightCM.co<br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:jwright@wrightcm.co">jwright@wrightcm.co</a><br />
    Mailing Address: 1 E Erie St, Suite 525-2110, Chicago, IL 60611</p>
  </div></div></section>

  <style>
    .legal{max-width:820px;margin:0 auto}
    .legal h2{font-size:1.3rem;margin:36px 0 10px}
    .legal h3{font-size:1.02rem;margin:22px 0 6px;color:var(--navy)}
    .legal p{color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:14px;font-size:1.02rem}
    .legal ul{margin:0 0 16px 22px;color:var(--muted)}
    .legal li{margin-bottom:7px}
    .legal a{color:var(--navy-2);font-weight:600}
    .legal a:hover{color:var(--red)}
  </style>
</Base>
